## What Changed

The full `analytics-go` repo was cloned and rebranded:

| Before | After |
|--------|-------|
| `github.com/amplitude/analytics-go` | `github.com/acai/analytics-go` |
| `amplitude/` package directory | `acai/` package directory |
| `amplitude_plugin.go`, `amplitude_http_client.go`, etc. | `acai_plugin.go`, `acai_http_client.go`, etc. |
| Amplitude server URLs | Your configurable `ServerURL` |
| All struct/type names (`AmplitudePlugin`, etc.) | `AcaiPlugin`, `AcaiHTTPClient`, etc. |

---

## Steps to Publish & Use the SDK

### 1. Push to GitHub
```bash
tar -xzf acai-analytics-go.tar.gz
cd acai-analytics-go
git init
git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR-ORG/analytics-go
git add . && git commit -m "Initial Acai SDK"
git push -u origin main
git tag v1.3.0 && git push --tags
```

### 2. Users install your SDK
```bash
go get github.com/YOUR-ORG/analytics-go
```
> Update `go.mod` to `module github.com/YOUR-ORG/analytics-go` before publishing.

### 3. Users point to your server
```go
import "github.com/YOUR-ORG/analytics-go/acai"

config := acai.NewConfig("YOUR-API-KEY")
config.ServerURL = "https://your-acai-server.com/2/httpapi"  // ← your server

client := acai.NewClient(config)
defer client.Shutdown()

client.Track(acai.Event{
    EventType: "Button Clicked",
    UserID:    "user-123",
})
```

### 4. Your server must accept this JSON payload
```json
POST /2/httpapi
{
  "api_key": "...",
  "events": [{ "event_type": "...", "user_id": "...", "time": 1700000000000 }]
}
```
Respond with `{"code": 200}` and status 200. The README has a minimal Go server example to get you started.